'''开放技术基金会'''（{{lang-en|Open Technology Fund}}，简称'''OTF'''）是美国的非营利公司<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.opentech.fund/news/new-independent-otf/|title=A New, Independent OTF|website=Open Technology Fund|language=en|access-date=2019-11-26|archive-date=2021-02-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210221010821/https://www.opentech.fund/news/new-independent-otf/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，原为[[自由亚洲电台|自由亚洲电台]]运营的项目<ref name=":0" />，旨在支持全球[[網路自由|網路自由]]技术，职责为“支持推广言论自由、突破[[审查制度|审查制度]]、对抗压迫性[[监视|监视]]手段的开放技术及社群，推动人权及开放社会发展”<ref name="values-principles">{{cite web|url=https://www.opentech.fund/about/values-principles/|title=Values & Principles|website=Open Technology Fund|access-date=2019-10-20|archive-date=2020-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126032911/https://www.opentech.fund/about/values-principles/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2019年11月，开放技术基金会改制为独立非营利公司，接受[[美国国际媒体署|美国国际媒体署]]捐赠<ref name=":0" />。

==历史==
开放技术基金会于2012年成立，是[[自由亚洲电台|自由亚洲电台]]旗下的试点计划<ref name="otf-history"/><ref name=":0" />。在[[美国国务卿|美国国务卿]][[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]的提议下，[[美国国务院|美国国务院]]通过一项支持全球互联网自由的倡议<ref name="Lake-2015-09-18"/>。当时，自由亚洲电台开始研究技术，帮助观众躲避审查及监视<ref name="Lake-2015-09-18" />。记者埃利·雷克（Eli Lake）认为，克林顿的政策“很大程度上受到在2009年[[伊朗绿色革命|伊朗绿色革命]]和2010年及2011年[[阿拉伯之春|阿拉伯之春]]中起推动作用的[[网络行动主义|网络行动主义]]影响”<ref name="Lake-2015-09-18">{{cite web|last1=Lake|first1=Eli|title=Government Is Fighting Itself on Encryption|url=http://www.bloombergview.com/articles/2015-09-18/government-is-fighting-itself-on-encryption|website=Bloomberg View|publisher=Bloomberg L.P.|type=Column|access-date=2016-02-15|date=2015-09-18|archive-date=2016-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160408195551/http://www.bloombergview.com/articles/2015-09-18/government-is-fighting-itself-on-encryption|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2014年9月，开放技术基金会与[[Google|Google]]和[[Dropbox|Dropbox]]合作，成立Simply Secure组织，改善隐私工具的易用性<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rushe|first1=Dominic|title=Google and Dropbox launch Simply Secure to improve online security|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/sep/18/google-dropbox-simply-secure-security-tech|website=The Guardian|publisher=Guardian Media Group|access-date=2016-02-14|date=2014-09-18|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111205109/http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/sep/18/google-dropbox-simply-secure-security-tech|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2017年3月，由于特朗普政府对网络自由议题的态度不明确，开放技术基金会被指受到质疑<ref>{{cite web|last1=Melendez|first1=Steven|title=U.S.-Backed Efforts To Promote Openness And Democracy Are At Risk In The Age Of Trump|url=https://www.fastcompany.com/3068328/us-backed-efforts-to-promote-openness-and-democracy-are-at-risk-in-the-age-of-trump|website=Fast Company|publisher=Fast Company, Inc|date=2017-03-24|accessdate=2021-02-28|archive-date=2020-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809205348/https://www.fastcompany.com/3068328/us-backed-efforts-to-promote-openness-and-democracy-are-at-risk-in-the-age-of-trump|dead-url=no}}</ref>。尽管如此，基金会仍继续接受国会的资助。

2019年11月，基金会改制为独立非营利公司<ref name=":0"/>。

==项目==
开放技术基金会资助第三方人士{{le|信息技术安全审计|Information technology security audit|审计}}所支持的[[源代码|源代码]]相关计划<ref name="code-audits"/>。而其他非开放技术基金会的计划，若有受审查制度或监视手段威胁的人士或组织使用，也会获得基金会的审计资金支持<ref name="code-audits"/>。基金会支持的计划中，较为知名的有[[Cryptocat|Cryptocat]]<ref>{{cite web|first1=Alban|last1=Diquet|first2=David|last2=Thiel|first3=Scott|last3=Stender|title=Open Technology Fund CryptoCat iOS Application Penetration Test|url=https://isecpartners.github.io/publications/iSEC_Cryptocat_iOS.pdf|publisher=iSEC Partners|access-date=2016-02-13|date=2014-02-07|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112023318/http://isecpartners.github.io/publications/iSEC_Cryptocat_iOS.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>、{{le|Commotion Wireless|Commotion Wireless}}<ref name="isecpartners-2013"/>、[[TextSecure|TextSecure]]<ref name="isecpartners-2013">{{cite web |title=Working with the Open Technology Fund |url=https://isecpartners.github.io/2013/10/14/open-tech-fund-report-release.html |first1=Tom |last1=Ritter |publisher=iSEC Partners |date=2013-10-14 |access-date=2016-02-13 |archive-date=2019-10-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191008001831/https://isecpartners.github.io/2013/10/14/open-tech-fund-report-release.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[GlobaLeaks|GlobaLeaks]]<ref name="isecpartners-2013"/>、[[MediaWiki|MediaWiki]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Steipp|first1=Chris|title=Improving the security of our users on Wikimedia sites|url=https://blog.wikimedia.org/2015/04/20/improving-security-for-our-users/|website=Wikimedia Blog|publisher=Wikimedia Foundation|access-date=2016-02-13|date=2015-04-20|archive-date=2020-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200630004258/https://blog.wikimedia.org/2015/04/20/improving-security-for-our-users/|dead-url=no}}</ref>、OpenPGP.js<ref>{{cite web|last1=Heiderich|first1=Mario|last2=Kotowicz|first2=Krzysztof|last3=Magazinius|first3=Jonas|last4=Antesberger|first4=Franz|title=Pentest-Report OpenPGP.js 02.2014|url=https://cure53.de/pentest-report_openpgpjs.pdf|publisher=Cure53|access-date=2016-02-14|date=2014-02|archive-date=2020-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130224909/https://cure53.de/pentest-report_openpgpjs.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>、{{tsl|en|Nitrokey|Nitrokey}}<ref>{{Cite web|last1=McDevitt|first1=Dan|title=Nitrokey Storage Firmware and Hardware Security Audits|url=https://www.opentech.fund/article/nitrokey-storage-firmware-and-hardware-security-audits|publisher=Open Technology Fund|access-date=2016-02-15|date=2015-10-02|archive-date=2017-06-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170620143747/https://www.opentech.fund/article/nitrokey-storage-firmware-and-hardware-security-audits|dead-url=no}}</ref>、{{tsl|en|Ricochet (software)|Ricochet (软件)|Ricochet}}<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cox|first1=Joseph|title='Ricochet', the Messenger That Beats Metadata, Passes Security Audit|url=http://motherboard.vice.com/read/ricochet-encrypted-messenger-tackles-metadata-problem-head-on|website=Motherboard|publisher=Vice Media LLC|access-date=2016-02-17|date=2016-02-17|archive-date=2017-01-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170123013927/https://motherboard.vice.com/read/ricochet-encrypted-messenger-tackles-metadata-problem-head-on|dead-url=no}}</ref>和[[TrueCrypt|TrueCrypt]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=White|first1=Kenneth|last2=Green|first2=Matthew|title=IsTrueCryptAuditedYet?|url=http://istruecryptauditedyet.com/|website=Open Crypto Audit Project|access-date=2016-02-14|date=2014-01-21|archive-date=2021-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215205627/http://istruecryptauditedyet.com/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2014年，基金会表示，成立三年来，已资助30多位科技代码审计员，确定了OTF和非OTF资助项目中的185个隐私和安全漏洞<ref name="code-audits">{{cite web|last1=Hurley|first1=Chad|title=Code Audits are Good. Making Code Audits Public is Better|url=https://www.opentech.fund/article/code-audits-are-good-making-code-audits-public-better|website=Open Technology Fund|access-date=2016-02-14|date=2014-12-10|archive-date=2018-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180320152025/https://www.opentech.fund/article/code-audits-are-good-making-code-audits-public-better|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2015年，[[Tor项目|Tor项目]]宣布基金会将资助{{tsl|en|HackerOne|HackerOne}}推广的{{tsl|en|bug bounty program|漏洞赏金计划}}<ref name="tor-bounty">{{cite web|last1=Cox|first1=Joseph|title=The Tor Project Is Starting a Bug Bounty Program|url=http://motherboard.vice.com/read/the-tor-project-is-starting-a-bug-bounty-program|website=Motherboard|publisher=Vice Media LLC|access-date=2016-02-14|date=2015-12-29|archive-date=2017-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129172603/https://motherboard.vice.com/read/the-tor-project-is-starting-a-bug-bounty-program|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Conditt|first1=Jessica|title=Tor plans to launch a bug bounty program|url=https://www.engadget.com/2015/12/31/tor-plans-to-launch-a-bug-bounty-program/|website=Engadget|publisher=AOL Inc.|access-date=2016-02-14|date=2015-12-31|archive-date=2016-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160211164437/http://www.engadget.com/2015/12/31/tor-plans-to-launch-a-bug-bounty-program/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。计划最初采用邀请制注册，职责为找出The Tor Project应用的漏洞<ref name="tor-bounty"/>。

2019年10月，基金会技术总监莎拉·奥恩（Sarah Aoun）向[[ABC新闻|ABC新闻]]报告了该会资助Cure53的研究计划，在中国政府推出的手机应用程序“[[学习强国|学习强国]]”中的发现<ref>{{cite web |title=Studying “Study the Great Nation” |url=https://www.opentech.fund/news/studying-study-the-great-nation/ |website=Open Technology Fund |accessdate=2021-02-28 |date=2019-10-12 |archive-date=2021-01-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210131020338/https://www.opentech.fund/news/studying-study-the-great-nation/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，表示该应用实质上把手机变成了“口袋监控设备”<ref name="Thorbecke-2019">{{cite web|url=https://www.goodmorningamerica.com/news/story/chinas-popular-education-app-surveillance-device-pocket-advocacy-66262334|title=China's popular education app is a 'surveillance device in your pocket,' advocacy group says|last1=Thorbecke|first1=Catherine|date=2019-10-18|website=Good Morning America|accessdate=2021-02-28|archive-date=2019-10-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191019113806/https://www.goodmorningamerica.com/news/story/chinas-popular-education-app-surveillance-device-pocket-advocacy-66262334|dead-url=no}}</ref>。研究总监亚当·林恩（Adam Lynn）告诉《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》：“（这个应用）调用（的权限）本身就明显......他们花了很大力气（隐瞒这一切），只会仅以加深外界对这个议题的审视”<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/chinese-app-on-xis-ideology-allows-data-access-to-100-million-users-phones-report-says/2019/10/11/2d53bbae-eb4d-11e9-bafb-da248f8d5734_story.html|title=Chinese app on Xi's ideology allows data access to 100 million users' phones, report says|newspaper=The Washington Post|last=Fifield|first=Anna|date=2019-10-12|accessdate=2021-02-28|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128233418/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/chinese-app-on-xis-ideology-allows-data-access-to-100-million-users-phones-report-says/2019/10/11/2d53bbae-eb4d-11e9-bafb-da248f8d5734_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

基金会上层机构美国国际媒体署2019年发表的报告《开放技术基金会的影响》显示，全球每天有20亿人使用基金会资助的技术，超过三分之二的手机用户在设备中使用基金会孵化的技术<ref name=USAGM-OTF2019/>。基金会前首席执行官刘仚（Libby Liu）表示，“随着全世界的极权主义政府不断尝试控制其公民在网上所读、所写乃至所分享的内容，基金会在这个如此关键时刻，可谓是碰上了下阶段发展的好时机”<ref name=USAGM2019-11-25/>。在美国国际媒体署200亿美元的支持，基金会参与协助了香港[[反修例运动|反修例运动]]，直至中国政府于2020年6月推出[[港版国安法|港版国安法]]时，媒体署主任迈克尔·佩克（Michael Pack）将这笔资金冻结才告终<ref name=time-20200626>{{cite news |url=https://time.com/5860163/trump-hong-kong-funding-freeze/?amp=true |title=Trump Administration Freezes Funds Intended to Benefit Hong Kong Protesters |last=Perrigo |first=Billy |publisher=Time |date=2020-06-26 |access-date=2020-07-05 |archive-date=2021-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106230505/https://time.com/5860163/trump-hong-kong-funding-freeze/?amp=true |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=scmp-20200703>{{cite news |url=https://www.scmp.com/comment/opinion/article/3091438/us-has-been-exposed-funding-last-years-hong-kong-protests |title=US has been exposed for funding last year's Hong Kong protests |last=Lo |first=Alex |newspaper=South China Morning Post |date=2020-07-03 |access-date=2020-07-05 |archive-date=2021-02-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210216022325/https://www.scmp.com/comment/opinion/article/3091438/us-has-been-exposed-funding-last-years-hong-kong-protests |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 理事会风波 ==
2020年6月17日，新上任的美国国际媒体署主任迈克尔·佩克开除了基金会董事兼主席执行官刘仚<ref>{{Cite web|author=Jennifer Hansler and Brian Stelter|title='Wednesday night massacre' as Trump appointee takes over at global media agency|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/06/17/media/us-agency-for-global-media-michael-pack/index.html|access-date=2020-10-18|website=CNN|archive-date=2021-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215031602/https://www.cnn.com/2020/06/17/media/us-agency-for-global-media-michael-pack/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Trump-backed US global media agency chief under fire for purge|url=https://www.dw.com/en/trump-backed-us-global-media-agency-chief-under-fire-for-purge/a-53870348|date=2020-06-19|access-date=2020-10-17|website=Deutsche Welle|language=en-GB|archive-date=2021-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210222091159/https://www.dw.com/en/trump-backed-us-global-media-agency-chief-under-fire-for-purge/a-53870348|dead-url=no}}</ref>。刘仚此前因就闭源软件使用问题于2020年6月13日递交辞呈，7月13日生效<ref>{{Cite web|last=Cox|first=Joseph|date=2020-06-17|title=CEO of Open Technology Fund Resigns After Closed-Source Lobbying Effort|url=https://www.vice.com/en_ca/article/935k5p/open-technology-fund-ceo-resigns|access-date=2020-06-17|website=Vice|language=en|archive-date=2020-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200702010234/https://www.vice.com/en_ca/article/935k5p/open-technology-fund-ceo-resigns|dead-url=no}}</ref>。6月23日，华盛顿哥伦比亚特区总检察长办公室提起诉讼，依照《哥伦比亚特区非营利企业法》，对这项人事变动提出异议。诉状指，有关行为违反了联邦通讯法规保护政府新闻机构不受政治干预的“防火墙”条款<ref>{{Cite news|last=Verma|first=Pranshu|date=2020-06-23|title=Lawsuit Argues Dismissal of Government-Funded Media Employees Was Unlawful|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/23/us/politics/michael-pack-global-media.html|access-date=2020-10-17|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2021-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201075928/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/23/us/politics/michael-pack-global-media.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。7月21日，[[美国哥伦比亚特区联邦巡回上诉法院|美国哥伦比亚特区联邦巡回上诉法院]]紧急暂停审理，封锁了案件的证据。法院的命令指，这些行为可能会威胁到在受政府压制国家对抗互联网审查的工作者<ref>{{Cite news|last=Hsu|first=Spencer S.|title=Appeals court blocks Trump administration takeover of organization fighting digital censorship and surveillance|language=en-US|work=Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/legal-issues/appeals-court-blocks-trump-administration-takeover-of-organization-fighting-digital-censorship-and-surveillance/2020/07/21/4f4299c4-cb5d-11ea-bc6a-6841b28d9093_story.html|access-date=2020-10-17|issn=0190-8286|archive-date=2021-01-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210112135416/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/legal-issues/appeals-court-blocks-trump-administration-takeover-of-organization-fighting-digital-censorship-and-surveillance/2020/07/21/4f4299c4-cb5d-11ea-bc6a-6841b28d9093_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。10月16日，在另一起案件中，特区高级法院裁定有关人事变动违法，新董事会所作任何变更均无效，恢复原董事会<ref>{{Cite web|first=Jerreat|last=Jessica|title=DC Court Rules in Dispute Over Open Technology Fund Board|url=https://www.voanews.com/usa/dc-court-rules-dispute-over-open-technology-fund-board|access-date=2020-10-17|website=VOA News|language=en|archive-date=2020-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201029180246/https://www.voanews.com/usa/dc-court-rules-dispute-over-open-technology-fund-board|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Summary Judgment DC v Pack|url=https://oag.dc.gov/sites/default/files/2020-10/OTF-Summary-Judgment.pdf|website=Office of the Attorney General for the District of Columbia|accessdate=2021-02-28|archive-date=2020-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022210213/https://oag.dc.gov/sites/default/files/2020-10/OTF-Summary-Judgment.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

自2020年8月起，基金会便不断受到佩克及媒体署领导层的压力<ref>{{cite news |last1=Allen-Ebrahamian |first1=Bethany |title=In media agency shakeup, conservative groups push for Falun Gong-backed internet tools |url=https://www.axios.com/falun-gong-us-agency-global-media-001fcf52-95fa-43de-b0c7-0cd7cfc2918f.html |access-date=2021-01-18 |publisher=Axios.com |date=2020-06-23 |archive-date=2021-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122214534/https://www.axios.com/falun-gong-us-agency-global-media-001fcf52-95fa-43de-b0c7-0cd7cfc2918f.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Sewell |first1=Tia |title=Trump's War on the U.S. Agency for Global Media |url=https://www.lawfareblog.com/trumps-war-us-agency-global-media |access-date=2021-01-18 |publisher=Lawfare |date=2021-01-12 |archive-date=2021-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126075702/https://www.lawfareblog.com/trumps-war-us-agency-global-media |dead-url=no }}</ref>。据[[Axios|Axios]]披露，这是因为基金会不愿对[[法轮功|法轮功]]致力于对抗中国[[防火长城|防火长城]]的企业，延长拨款期；《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》则指法轮功及旗下的《[[大纪元时报|大纪元时报]]》媒体集团经常公开支持特朗普政府<ref>{{cite news |last1=Roose |first1=Kevin |title=Epoch Times, Punished by Facebook, Gets a New Megaphone on YouTube |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/05/technology/epoch-times-youtube.html |access-date=2021-01-18 |work=New York Times |date=2020-02-05 |archive-date=2020-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206140610/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/05/technology/epoch-times-youtube.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。8月8日，媒体署自行成立互联网自由办公室，放宽拨款条件，并开始请求基金会的受赠者到新办公室申请捐赠<ref>{{cite web |title=CEO Pack revives USAGM's Office of Internet Freedom; agency funds internet firewall circumvention technologies |url=https://www.usagm.gov/2020/08/18/ceo-pack-revives-usagms-office-of-internet-freedom-agency-funds-internet-firewall-circumvention-technologies/ |website=US Agency for Global Media |access-date=2021-01-18 |archive-date=2021-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122183735/https://www.usagm.gov/2020/08/18/ceo-pack-revives-usagms-office-of-internet-freedom-agency-funds-internet-firewall-circumvention-technologies/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Fischer |first1=Sara |title=Scoop: USAGM soliciting OTF partners as it withholds funds |url=https://www.axios.com/usagm-soliciting-otf-partners-as-it-withholds-funds-e59fa0d1-5ec9-4fcc-a5c1-64176fa23644.html |access-date=2021-01-18 |publisher=Axios.com |date=2020-10-13 |archive-date=2021-01-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116131953/https://www.axios.com/usagm-soliciting-otf-partners-as-it-withholds-funds-e59fa0d1-5ec9-4fcc-a5c1-64176fa23644.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。8月20日，基金会向美国联邦法院起诉媒体署，要求对方扣缴先前商定的近2000万美元的赠款<ref>{{cite news |last1=Fischer |first1=Sara |title=Scoop: Open Technology Fund sues administration for $20M in missing funds |url=https://www.axios.com/scoop-open-technology-fund-sues-administration-for-20m-in-missing-funds-90b5420d-2f41-4e50-b58b-6a517af26cd6.html |access-date=2021-01-18 |publisher=Axios.com |date=2020-08-20 |archive-date=2021-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126144044/https://www.axios.com/scoop-open-technology-fund-sues-administration-for-20m-in-missing-funds-90b5420d-2f41-4e50-b58b-6a517af26cd6.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

